ing to\ntake an action (setting the price), and a state of nature (the buyer's type)\ndrawn from a common prior. We show that it is NP-hard to approximate the\noptimal sender's utility to within any constant factor in the presence of\ncommunication constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Jun 2016 22:08:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Mar 2020 22:59:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-09"}
